main event: A tear-shaped object was observed falling from west to east in Cloquet, Minnesota on April 23, 1963.
interesting points: The object was the size of a football and observed for 5 seconds,It had a bright tail and made no sound,The object was described as a bluish flash,The incident appears to be an ordinary meteor according to the report,The sighting was confirmed by a chief of guards at a local wood conversion company.
witness description: chief of guards at Wood Conversion Co.
